<span id="iv.vii.xiv"></span>

<span id="iv.vii.xiv-p1"></span> 14. It follows after commendation of
the Trinity, “The Holy Church.” God is pointed out, and His temple. “For
the temple of God is holy,” says the Apostle, “which (temple) are
ye.” <span id="fr_1800"></span>[1801](#fn_1800.md) This same is the holy
Church, the one Church, the true Church, the catholic Church, fighting
against all heresies: fight, it can: be fought down, it cannot. As for
heresies, they went all out of it, like as unprofitable branches pruned
from the vine: but itself abideth in its root, in its Vine, in its
charity. “The gates of hell shall not prevail against it.” <span
id="fr_1801"></span>[1802](#fn_1801.md)

